34
00:01:49.160 --> 00:01:51.480
Money mules, so what are they?

35
00:01:51.480 --> 00:01:54.520
I'm here to talk to you about how criminals

36
00:01:54.520 --> 00:01:56.960
use money mules to move money.

37
00:01:56.960 --> 00:02:01.880
So let's start at the beginning and try
to explain what a money mule actually is.

38
00:02:01.880 --> 00:02:07.640
A money mule is someone who lets criminals
use their bank accounts to move money.

39
00:02:07.640 --> 00:02:10.960
Often that mule doesn't know
what's really happening

40
00:02:10.960 --> 00:02:15.280
and has been manipulated
into believing a cover story

41
00:02:15.280 --> 00:02:19.120
or lured by an offer of a repayment.

42
00:02:19.120 --> 00:02:21.880
There are two main types of money mules.

43
00:02:21.880 --> 00:02:23.480
One of those will be witting.

44
00:02:23.480 --> 00:02:28.280
Witting mules are generally complicit with the crime.

45
00:02:28.280 --> 00:02:31.200
They are aware
of the criminal source of funds

46
00:02:31.200 --> 00:02:36.200
and typically they can be recruited
using social media platforms.

47
00:02:36.200 --> 00:02:40.640
Most commonly Instagram, WhatsApp
or Snapchat.

48
00:02:40.640 --> 00:02:44.800
Account holders are generally lured
by quick cash opportunities

49
00:02:44.800 --> 00:02:48.120
and will disclose their
account security details,

50
00:02:48.120 --> 00:02:52.680
payment cards and PINs
in exchange for monetary rewards.

51
00:02:52.680 --> 00:02:57.000
They may also receive
and send on criminal funds themselves,

52
00:02:57.000 --> 00:03:02.440
but generally they're aware
that what they're doing is actually wrong.

53
00:03:02.440 --> 00:03:04.520
Then on the flip side, there’s the unwitting.

54
00:03:04.520 --> 00:03:10.200
These individuals engage in mule
activity generally under false pretences.

55
00:03:10.200 --> 00:03:14.760
It could involve exploitation, where they're
duped into distributing payments,

56
00:03:14.760 --> 00:03:17.440
while actually being scammed themselves.

57
00:03:18.560 --> 00:03:21.400
You might also have heard
the term ‘mule herder’.

58
00:03:21.400 --> 00:03:23.760
So what is a mule herder?

59
00:03:23.760 --> 00:03:28.920
Well, they are the key support
to the criminal gangs as it's them

60
00:03:28.920 --> 00:03:33.560
who recruit the actual money
mule to do the job for them.

61
00:03:33.560 --> 00:03:37.840
They do that by searching
your social media profile for information

62
00:03:37.840 --> 00:03:42.680
and then use it to befriend you, or trick
you into receiving stolen money

63
00:03:43.400 --> 00:03:44.720
into your bank account.

64
00:03:44.720 --> 00:03:48.960
That's the key thing that a mule herder
is looking for - you to have a bank account.

65
00:03:48.960 --> 00:03:51.840
They might approach you online
through a messaging app

66
00:03:51.840 --> 00:03:56.680
or actually in person at the school gates
or in the workplace or at university.

67
00:03:57.440 --> 00:04:00.440
They are importantly the link
between the mule

68
00:04:00.440 --> 00:04:01.840
and the organised crime gangs,

69
00:04:01.840 --> 00:04:06.360
or OCG’s as we call them,
along with law enforcement.

70
00:04:06.360 --> 00:04:10.040
These OCG's could be funding
terrorism across the world

71
00:04:10.040 --> 00:04:13.760
like drugs or human
trafficking - sexual exploitation.

72
00:04:13.760 --> 00:04:19.520
And it scares me to think of the innocent
people encountering these dangerous individuals.

73
00:04:20.280 --> 00:04:24.320
So what does money mule activity
actually look like?

74
00:04:24.320 --> 00:04:27.360
Mule herders
tend to lie to get what they want.

75
00:04:27.360 --> 00:04:31.440
They might say it's quick and easy
and, you know,

76
00:04:31.440 --> 00:04:35.760
no ramifications involved in doing it.

77
00:04:35.760 --> 00:04:40.640
And it's an easy way to make money, or that
they urgently need to receive a payment.

78
00:04:40.640 --> 00:04:43.200
And you're the only one who can help them.

79
00:04:43.200 --> 00:04:46.440
But they can't use their own account
for whatever reason.

80
00:04:46.440 --> 00:04:51.200
They might even offer a cash or
gifts as a reward or incentive.

81
00:04:51.200 --> 00:04:56.200
The herder will use that cover story
as an excuse to pass you that stolen money.

82
00:04:56.800 --> 00:04:59.960
They might ask you to open
a bank account yourself,

83
00:04:59.960 --> 00:05:01.400
if you don't already have one.

84
00:05:01.400 --> 00:05:06.000
They might transfer money to you
or give you cash to pay into your account.

85
00:05:06.000 --> 00:05:09.640
They could ask you to
pass it on by a bank transfer,

86
00:05:09.640 --> 00:05:13.640
or withdraw it as cash,
or even ask you to buy,

87
00:05:13.640 --> 00:05:17.400
to purchase a high value item
in exchange for the money.

88
00:05:17.400 --> 00:05:20.600
Importantly, passed back
to the criminal network.

89
00:05:20.600 --> 00:05:23.480
They might ask for your
online banking details

90
00:05:23.480 --> 00:05:28.880
so that they can do the activities
themselves on your own account.

91
00:05:28.880 --> 00:05:33.160
Or they might ask for an activation code
to access your banking app.

92
00:05:33.160 --> 00:05:36.640
But importantly, it lets them
access your account

93
00:05:36.640 --> 00:05:39.480
and use it to clean their dirty money.

94
00:05:39.480 --> 00:05:43.600
Which means to essentially confuse
the origin of the funds

95
00:05:43.600 --> 00:05:47.560
and to make those funds appear genuine.

96
00:05:47.560 --> 00:05:50.720
They also could actually buy
an item from you

97
00:05:50.720 --> 00:05:52.960
and ask to pay by bank transfer.

98
00:05:52.960 --> 00:05:57.440
But the important thing is they tend
to pay from a stolen account

99
00:05:57.440 --> 00:06:02.200
and you give them the item and often
you can lose those funds

100
00:06:02.200 --> 00:06:05.240
once the criminal nature of them
is understood

101
00:06:05.240 --> 00:06:07.680
by the banking system.

102
00:06:07.680 --> 00:06:11.560
So is it a crime to act as a money mule?

103
00:06:11.640 --> 00:06:14.040
Well, absolutely. Yes, it is.

104
00:06:14.040 --> 00:06:18.560
Unfortunately, handling money
that comes from illegal activity is a crime,

105
00:06:18.560 --> 00:06:20.800
even if you don't know what you're doing.

106
00:06:20.800 --> 00:06:23.040
Money can often be traced

107
00:06:23.040 --> 00:06:26.920
to someone who has been the
victim of a scam or a fraud.

108
00:06:26.920 --> 00:06:30.720
I'm sure we all know someone
who has been affected by a scam

109
00:06:30.720 --> 00:06:33.520
at some point in the past.

110
00:06:33.840 --> 00:06:37.480
Whether they're old or
young, vulnerable or not,

111
00:06:37.480 --> 00:06:41.840
UK Finance, who are the trade
association for the banking industry,

112
00:06:41.840 --> 00:06:45.920
have advised that over £1.2 billion

113
00:06:45.920 --> 00:06:49.120
was stolen through fraud last year.

114
00:06:49.120 --> 00:06:54.680
That's the equivalent of
over £2,300 every minute.

115
00:06:54.880 --> 00:06:57.880
Most importantly, if we didn't have mules,

116
00:06:57.880 --> 00:07:02.480
there would not be a route to take
a lot of those funds from those victims.

117
00:07:02.480 --> 00:07:05.200
They simply wouldn't be able to operate.

118
00:07:06.680 --> 00:07:09.960
If you are a mule, the
consequences can range from

119
00:07:09.960 --> 00:07:14.040
your bank account being closed,
to even going to prison.

120
00:07:14.040 --> 00:07:16.720
But what is the reality of getting caught

121
00:07:16.720 --> 00:07:20.280
and what impact could this have
on your lifestyle or your future?

122
00:07:21.920 --> 00:07:26.080
For most people, getting caught means
that your bank account could be closed

123
00:07:26.080 --> 00:07:29.200
and you'll have problems opening a new one.

124
00:07:29.640 --> 00:07:33.480
That makes paying your basic
living expenses so much harder,

125
00:07:33.480 --> 00:07:36.560
removes any independence that you might have.

126
00:07:37.160 --> 00:07:40.080
You could find it difficult to get credit

127
00:07:40.080 --> 00:07:44.080
like a student loan, phone contract,
or a mortgage or a loan.

128
00:07:44.080 --> 00:07:46.160
You could end up with a criminal record

129
00:07:46.160 --> 00:07:50.640
and that could affect your ability
to get a job or to go to university.

130
00:07:51.240 --> 00:07:55.000
But you could also go to prison
for up to 14 years.

131
00:07:55.880 --> 00:07:59.240
So it's important that
you know the warning signs -

132
00:07:59.240 --> 00:08:00.920
the red flags to look out for.

133
00:08:00.920 --> 00:08:05.400
This can help you identify mule herders
and avoid falling for their tricks.

134
00:08:08.600 --> 00:08:11.760
Or contact from someone that you don't know

135
00:08:11.760 --> 00:08:14.800
trying to befriend you,

136
00:08:14.800 --> 00:08:18.640
especially online or through
a messaging app.

137
00:08:18.640 --> 00:08:23.000
Look out for someone you may also, who may
also ask you to move money for them.

138
00:08:23.000 --> 00:08:28.680
Always check that you know
where the funds have come from.

139
00:08:28.680 --> 00:08:30.720
Look out for anyone
you've met online, 

140
00:08:30.720 --> 00:08:33.240
offering deals that sound
too good to be true.

141
00:08:33.240 --> 00:08:34.800
It often is.

142
00:08:34.800 --> 00:08:38.080
Be suspicious of jobs offering
quick and easy money

143
00:08:38.080 --> 00:08:40.480
with no experience necessary.

144
00:08:40.480 --> 00:08:44.160
Be wary of anyone who
asks to transfer money

145
00:08:44.160 --> 00:08:48.040
to your bank account for you
to pass on to another account.

146
00:08:48.040 --> 00:08:50.840
And take care when selling an item,

147
00:08:50.840 --> 00:08:54.280
where the buyer insists on
paying by bank transfer

148
00:08:54.280 --> 00:08:56.760
or pressuring you for a quick sale.

149
00:08:56.760 --> 00:08:59.960
Or even paying over the odds,
that's not usual.

150
00:09:00.920 --> 00:09:05.880
So what are Barclays
doing to target mules?

151
00:09:05.880 --> 00:09:08.120
We focus on prevention.

152
00:09:08.120 --> 00:09:10.080
If we can prevent a mule,

153
00:09:10.080 --> 00:09:14.400
we can prevent a potential scam,
and that means less victims.

154
00:09:14.400 --> 00:09:17.680
We do this by providing targeted education

155
00:09:17.680 --> 00:09:21.040
to our colleagues and customers
on how to protect themselves.

156
00:09:21.040 --> 00:09:25.880
Our priority is to protect our customers
as well as society in general

157
00:09:25.880 --> 00:09:31.000
of the dangers presented by criminal gangs
who are at the heart of this problem.

158
00:09:31.000 --> 00:09:36.120
Last year, 43% of mule cases
identified by Barclays

159
00:09:36.120 --> 00:09:39.200
were individuals under the age of 25.

160
00:09:39.200 --> 00:09:42.560
So we tend to do lots of targeted messages

161
00:09:42.560 --> 00:09:45.120
in those younger age categories.

162
00:09:45.120 --> 00:09:48.520
The children's digital banking
market is expanding.

163
00:09:48.520 --> 00:09:53.040
UK finance revealed that the number
of 14 to 18-year-olds

164
00:09:53.040 --> 00:09:58.960
misusing their bank account
rose by 73% in the last two years.

165
00:09:58.960 --> 00:10:02.120
There are even reports of children
as young as 12

166
00:10:02.120 --> 00:10:06.080
being persuaded to comply
with the misuse of their accounts.

167
00:10:07.080 --> 00:10:09.640
If we can't prevent
someone being recruited,

168
00:10:09.640 --> 00:10:13.120
we do also monitor payments
and react in the moment

169
00:10:13.120 --> 00:10:18.080
as time is of the essence to trap criminal
funds before the mule can move them.

170
00:10:18.440 --> 00:10:20.760
We also work with many suppliers

171
00:10:20.960 --> 00:10:24.720
who provide a range of
ways to detect money mules.

172
00:10:25.200 --> 00:10:28.360
But more than ever,
we're sharing more information

173
00:10:28.360 --> 00:10:31.960
across the banking industry
to jointly tackle the problem.

174
00:10:31.960 --> 00:10:35.120
There is more government
regulation coming to banks,

175
00:10:35.120 --> 00:10:39.240
which compels the whole industry to
collaborate and work together.

176
00:10:39.920 --> 00:10:43.160
Over the first six months of 2023,

177
00:10:43.160 --> 00:10:50.440
17,286 cases involving money
mule activities were filed.

178
00:10:52.400 --> 00:10:58.920
And that includes 3,881
people under the age of 21.

179
00:10:59.840 --> 00:11:01.920
A growing number of
other age groups 

180
00:11:01.920 --> 00:11:05.240
are also being recruited
by criminal gangs too.

181
00:11:05.320 --> 00:11:08.320
Between 2017 and 2021

182
00:11:08.520 --> 00:11:11.680
we've seen a 34% increase
in the number of accounts

183
00:11:11.680 --> 00:11:16.160
belonging to 40 to 60-year-olds
displaying money mule activity.

184
00:11:16.240 --> 00:11:18.160
That's really unusual.

185
00:11:19.080 --> 00:11:21.720
But obviously, in trying to target all areas 

186
00:11:21.720 --> 00:11:24.880
and all age groups in
which mule operates,

187
00:11:24.880 --> 00:11:26.920
we know that genuine customers

188
00:11:26.920 --> 00:11:30.800
can sometimes be impacted
as we try to look for suspicion.

189
00:11:30.800 --> 00:11:36.120
So it may be that we have to
delay payment sometimes

190
00:11:36.120 --> 00:11:41.160
just to check that we feel that
the origins of that payment are genuine.

191
00:11:41.160 --> 00:11:43.520
But a key priority for us is always

192
00:11:43.520 --> 00:11:46.520
to limit the impact on genuine customers.

193
00:11:46.520 --> 00:11:50.080
We want Barclays to make money work
for the genuine people,

194
00:11:50.080 --> 00:11:53.160
not the criminals.

195
00:11:53.240 --> 00:11:55.400
And with that  I'll hand
back to you, Ross.

196
00:11:55.400 --> 00:11:57.400
Thank you.

197
